    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "3. Frequency Configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "we should write CC_GP4 register to configure frequency."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3.1. PWM calculation"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Equations to calculate output frequency and M, N, D values. 1) 𝐹𝑜𝑢𝑡=𝐹𝑖𝑛 × 𝑀/𝑁 2) Give a value to M, trying to make N as an integer. 3) 𝑂𝑢𝑡𝑝𝑢𝑡 𝑑𝑢𝑡𝑦= 𝐷/𝑁, D is the number of input clock period for high voltage time of output clock. D should be less than N. (Currently only output duty = 50% is supported, other D value may not take effect.) 4) The value saved to N register is NOT (N - M) and the value saved to D register is NOT (2*D). Example: Output frequency 60 Hz duty 50%, selecting source clock 32768 Hz: 𝑁= 𝑀 ×3276860 , giving M = 15 can make N is an integer, N = 8192 D = N x 50% = 4096 The M/N/D registers are 16-bit width, calculate their programming value:"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20generate%20PWM%20for%20USS/image-2024-11-21_15-6-39.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to generate PWM for USS/image-2024-11-21_15-6-39.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3.2. Access Permissions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "GCC_GP4 register have been configured as read/written only in hypervisor mode (EL2), this was done by sailhyp.elf."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When change GCC_GP4 register in system mode (EL1), MPU trap will happen."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Two solutions:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Change GCC_GP4 register access permission to EL1. This should be done in sailhyp.elf by Qualcomm.",
        "Qualcomm provide an API to switch CPU running mode. eg: EL2 (hypervisor mode), EL1 (SYS), EL0."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Solution 2 is an universal approach, if solution 2 can be achieved, solution 1 is not needed."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3.3. Write sequence to configure GCC_GP4"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Configure SAIL_IO_46 to Output and alternative function= sailss_cc_gp4_clk_mira(3), DRV 16ma, PULL UP in Vector Mcal Tool.",
        "Update CFG_RCGR -> src 32.768khz, dual_edge, SRC_DIV=BYPASS out32 0x170008 0x102500",
        "Update M,N,D values according to 60Hz example # out32 0x17000c 0xF # out32 0x170010 0xE00E # out32 0x170014 0xDFFF",
        "Update CMD_RCGR -> UPDATE=1 # out32 0x170004 0x1",
        "Update CBCR to enable clk # out32 0x170000 0x1"
      ]
    },
